ce:section.ce:para:
Following the results obtained for simulated CDs samples, HPLC analyses were conducted for the real CDs samples. In this case the CDs samples were studied using two detection methods i.e. LC-MS and LC-FLD. For cys-CDs samples, TPA could be detected easily in raw sample solution as well as in purified samples using both detection methods (Table 2
                         and Fig. 4
                        ). Interestingly, HPPT could be determined in the ur-CDs-green sample dialyzed for 72 h with LC-FLD, while it was not detectable via LCMS nor 1H NMR. The most striking difference in the results obtained from NMR and chromatographic experiments was noticed for ur-CDs-blue samples. In case of both employed HPLC detection methods citrazinic acid was detected in all samples, even in those dialyzed for 72 h (Table 2 and Fig. 3). The concentrations of specific molecular fluorophores, estimated via LC-MS and LC-FLD in the studied real CDs samples, were summarized in Table 2. Note that at this stage the analyses were not intended to determine the absolute concentration of fluorophores in carbon dot samples, but merely to provide an indication of the CDs’ contamination levels with molecular fluorophores.
